    For example.

    If, updating emoncms via API, I'd argue, that should prob be handled by dedicated grain(s).
    
Readme/Project Goals-
    While this project originally started as a solution for polling near-real time data for individual devices on my PDUs, and fully integrating the vertiv rPDUs with my home assistant, I have given this project a bit of identity crisis, and introduced a bit of heavy vibe coding.

    The projects new purpose, is to handle mapping out the FULL energy flow across my house.

    (you will need to update this.... here is the gist.)
    ``` mermaid
    individual panels (via tigo)
    -> grouped into strings
    -> connected to MPPTs (via modbus, or mqtt)
    -> inverter output details (via modbus or mqtt)
    -> inverter -> battery
    -> gridboss/transfer switch details
    -> main panel, load shedding panel, shop panel, east HVAC panel, pool panel (electrical panels, load centers)
    -> per circuit metering for many of the meters, via Iotawatt, and other solutions
    -> per device monitoring, via S31 smart plugs (https://static.xtremeownage.com/blog/2023/sonoff-s31---low-cost-energy-monitoring/), vertiv RPDUs (https://static.xtremeownage.com/blog/2024/metered-switch-pdu/?), And other z-wave, zigbee, esphome/etc devices which can support metering their own power.
    ```

    The end goal, is tracking everything, from end, to end.

    Should you use it? Thats up to you. I built it for me, but, made it public, and tried to ensure it was at least half way documented.

    One of the reaons I built this, instead of using home assistant directly- I keep a lot of history on energy data. I have 6 years worth of per-circuit measurements from my old house, collected via my Iotawatt.... at a 15 second data interval. 

    I may never use this data. But, I like having this data incase I ever do need to use it. On more then one ocassion, an update to home assistant, or one of its plugins/containers/etc... has resulted in renamed entities breaking quite a few things for me. 

    [Here](https://static.xtremeownage.com/blog/2023/home-assistant---energy-flow-diagram/?) is one of my flow diagrams from a few years back. That was at my old location, which was quite a bit more simple..... and much smaller.

    Now- imagine, I have over 40 CT clamps to be deployed to various breaker panels, I have 5 different panels with breakers. And- I meter and measure everything.

    This solution faciliaites the management for me. It updates / creates items in home assistant. It updates the energy dashboards. It creates and updates the feeds in emoncms. And, it even exports metrics to prometheus, incase I wanted to use grafana for charting.